{
  "doc_id": "52694",
  "text": "Freeman et al. suggested that the rate of decline in the AMH rather than the absolute AMH level is useful in predicting the age of the menopause [CITATION_1] . Nikolaou et al. reported that women who had a poor response to ovarian stimulation were likely to develop menopausal symptoms within seven years [CITATION_2] . Lawson et al. reported that a poor ovarian response was a strong predictor for ovarian failure than elevated FSH [CITATION_3] .",
